<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-16T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="593" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d593">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.811/282a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-16T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            16, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>American International Corporation would like to carry on
                                negotiations relative to advance for preliminary canal survey
                                through channel of Chinese Legation here. Discreetly ascertain
                                whether His Excellency Hsiung Hsi-ling<note n="40" xml:id="d593fn40">Director General of the Grand Canal Improvement Board.</note>
                                would have any objection. Please inform Hitchcock<note n="41" xml:id="d593fn41">F. C. Hitchcock, Vice President of the
                                    Siems-Carey Railway &amp; Canal Co., in Peking.</note> and
                                    Gatrell.<note n="42" xml:id="d593fn42">T. J. N. Gatrell,
                                    representative of the Siems-Carey Railway &amp; Canal Co., in
                                    Peking.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>